Ad Text:
Be part of a high performing team
Location: Melbourne
Initial 6 months contract - multiple positions available
Hybrid

The opportunity

As a Senior Business Analyst, you will be responsible for the quality, planning and estimating of your individual workstream and deliverables. In addition to good technical BA capabilities, your role will require a comprehensive understanding of project delivery methodologies. You should have a good working knowledge of project management techniques, as well as an understanding of organisational change management, development and testing.



Description of division and business unit



The North Platforms Technology team sits within the Technology division within AMP.



The North Platforms Technology team provides full lifecycle management of the North platform which is one of the leading Wrap platforms in the Wealth market. The capability within the team is very diverse with specialised skillset and deep knowledge within the Wealth Industry. Roles within the team cover Strategic Planning, Business and Systems Analysis, Development, Architecture, Testing, and Production Support.



We work very closely with our business partners across the Client Services, Digital and Adviser Experience, Product, Distribution, Marketing, and other finance areas and have deep appreciation of how Technology plays a pivotal role in helping these partners achieve successful outcomes.

About the role:

Lead discussion between Business and Technology teams to understand business objectives and translate into solutions.
Work with the business leaders and across transformation and technology teams to plan and deliver change.
Working and delivering within Agile delivery frameworks, as well as mentoring and adapting to best practices.
Produce business and functional requirements for business and technology stakeholders and facilitate necessary reviews/approvals.
Work through the entire software development lifecycle, responsible for supporting both Business and Technology activities.
Lead and/or support the scoping and estimating of initiatives, including support for development of business cases.
Conduct impact assessments across the North Platform and with internal and external upstream/downstream systems.
Work with business and Tech Leads to ensure sequencing of delivery is efficient and supports required outcomes of both groups.
Support the transition of software changes to BAU, working with Change, Training Teams and Production Support.
Build and foster effective relationships with Business and IT teams internally and externally
Lead multiple initiatives simultaneously, ensuring timely and quality delivery.
Work autonomously while collaborating effectively with cross-functional teams.
Manage complex initiatives that require strong problem-solving and prioritization skills.
Drive continuous improvement of business analysis practices and processes.
Elicitation and documentation of business requirements, functional specifications and handovers. Facilitation of workshops, including capturing, summarising and organising inputs and outputs. Process analysis and mapping (As-Is, To-Be).
Scoping, estimating and planning streams of work.
Support the development of business cases.
Ability to engage with both business and technical resources and act as the conduit to deliver outcomes, doing so within hybrid Agile and Waterfall environments.

About you:

5+ years of experience of performing business analysis on large projects delivering business and technology change within the financial services industry.
Strong business analysis experience in wealth management, investment wraps or superannuation delivering complex projects.
Wrap platform experience or North experience highly valuable
Experience working across the end-to-end software development life cycle (SDLC) within both Agile and Waterfall delivery environments.
Strong experience in applying business analysis to drive strategic development and process improvement.
Excellent problem-solving skills.
Demonstrated experience leading analysis that creates new business capability.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
Ability to coach and mentor other Business Analysts to uplift team capability.
Proven experience managing multiple initiatives in parallel within dynamic environments.
Proficiency in JIRA, Confluence, and SQL.

Working at AMP



We are transforming our business. We are looking for people with courage, accountability and integrity who inspire the same in others. If you are comfortable challenging the status-quo and perform at your best in an evolving and complex environment - we need you.



Wellbeing & Benefits



We invest in the health, wellbeing, and development of all our people including our contingent professionals, by offering a range of great benefits to support you be your best, professionally, and personally:

Finance & investment assistance and opportunities.
Salary packaging and novated vehicle leases
Employee Assistance Program - Benestar.

Access to a range of discounted offerings via an extra's benefits program.
Networking / professional development opportunities and events

We are seeking an experienced Lead Digital Performance Analyst to support reporting, performance analysis, and data-driven decision making within a large and complex government environment. About the Role

As a Lead Digital Performance Analyst, you will be responsible for reviewing reporting and performance needs, identifying opportunities for improvement, and delivering high-quality analysis and reporting solutions. You will work closely with senior stakeholders to influence decisions and improve processes through better use of data.

Key Responsibilities
Develop automated reports, conduct in-depth analysis, and provide insights into key performance metrics

Produce high-level artefacts including business, process, and data flow diagrams (current and future state)

Develop and maintain technical and system documentation as required
Identify process inefficiencies, redundancies, and automation opportunities, and propose practical solutions
Skills and Experience

Essential:

Proven experience working with high-volume operational and transactional data
Strong analytical capability, including both qualitative and quantitative analysis
Experience analysing data across platforms such as Microsoft Azure
Demonstrated ability to gather requirements and define clear reporting specifications
Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to translate business needs into data-driven solutions
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to explain complex concepts in a clear and accessible way
Self-motivated, proactive, and able to work both independently and collaboratively

Highly Desirable:

Experience with Power BI
Strong SQL skills
Experience using Python and/or R
Selection Criteria

Candidates will be required to address the following criteria (responses required for each):

Gathering requirements and defining report specifications
Data modelling and data extraction from existing systems to support future enhancements or integrated data models
Working with transactional and point-in-time data
Mapping and visualising process pathways and identifying bottlenecks
Identifying metrics that contribute to process improvement

THE FUTURE IS WHAT WE MAKE IT. 

Lead Technical Product Owner

Sydney

Start your career by making an impact and real connections with some of the most meaningful challenges around. When you join Honeywell, you become a member of our performance culture comprised of diverse leaders, thinkers, innovators, dreamers, and doers who are changing the future. 

Make the Best You.

The Lead Technical Product Owner (LTPO) is a strategic leadership role responsible for defining and driving the product vision across the portfolio, with a focus on enterprise-scale solutions. This role ensures that product requirements are well-defined, technically feasible, and aligned with architectural standards to deliver innovative, secure, and scalable outcomes.

As the technical advocate for the product, the LTPO works closely with architects, engineering teams, stakeholders, and customers to design solutions that integrate modern technologies—including cloud-native platforms, IoT, and AI/ML—to deliver intelligent, data-driven building systems. The LTPO analyses customer requirements and translates them into actionable outcomes, ensuring solutions are aligned with business drivers and user needs.

In addition to leading product strategy, the LTPO mentors and enables a team of Technology Product Owners, fostering a high-performance culture that delivers on key business initiatives and customer commitments. The role also involves managing scope and driving trade-off decisions in conjunction with stakeholders, balancing business requirements with technical constraints to ensure optimal outcomes.

This is a leadership opportunity for someone who thrives on shaping product strategy, enabling agile teams, and delivering meaningful outcomes through technical innovation, operational excellence, and domain expertise in smart buildings.

Responsibilities:

Customer-Centric Analysis

Analyses customer requirements and translates them into actionable outcomes, ensuring solutions are aligned with business drivers and user needs.

Requirements Engineering

Roadmap & Feature Definition: Partners with Product Managers to evaluate the product roadmap, identify high-impact features for development, and define the “definition of done” for each deliverable.

Translate complex business needs into well-structured epics, features, and user stories with clear acceptance criteria. 

Lead backlog refinement sessions with cross-functional teams, ensuring technical dependencies and constraints are addressed.

Maintain traceability between business objectives & technical requirements

Technical Leadership

Define and evolve the product architecture in collaboration with Solution Architects and Engineering Leads.

Ensure technical feasibility and system integrity across all product increments.

Drive decisions on APIs, data models, integration patterns, and cloud-native design principles.

Domain Awareness

Maintains a strong understanding of the latest trends and technology shifts within the Buildings Domain, proactively identifying opportunities for innovation and improvement

Team Enablement & Mentorship

Mentor a team of Technology Product Owners, fostering a culture of ownership, continuous learning, and technical excellence.

Provide guidance on agile ceremonies, backlog prioritisation, and stakeholder engagement.

Facilitate knowledge sharing and technical upskilling across the product ownership community.

Stakeholder Engagement & Advocacy

Manage scope and drive trade-off decisions in conjunction with external stakeholders while balancing business requirements with technical requirements 

Act as the technical voice of the product in steering committees, architecture forums, and customer engagements.

Communicate product vision, technical strategy, and value to senior leadership and business stakeholders.

Advocate for customer value, system reliability, and operational efficiency in all product decisions.

Continuous Improvement

Analyze delivery metrics, incident trends, and customer feedback to identify areas for improvement.

AI/ML Leadership: Champions the adoption and integration of artificial intelligence and machine learning to deliver intelligent, data-driven product features that set new standards for customer value.

Qualifications:

Holds a Bachelor's degree or equivalent in engineering/computer science or equivalent discipline.

Proven experience as a Product Owner or Product Manager withing building automation, enterprise software or IoT solutions.

Solid understanding of system integration, IoT ecosystem, cloud platforms, and cybersecurity standards.

Skilled in stakeholder management and cross-functional leadership.

Ability to simplify complex technical concepts for business and customers.

Who We Are

The Future Is What We Make It at Honeywell. From sustainable aviation fuel and life-saving healthcare sensors to collaborating on every NASA space mission since the 1950’s, over 100 years of innovation has always been driven by an investment in our people. 

Learn more about Honeywell: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CG-rmG0eKLk

Discover More 

Our focus at Honeywell is innovation that drives business, improves the bottom line and creates solutions for our customers and communities around the world. There’s a lot for you to discover. Our solutions, our case studies, our #Futureshapers, and so much more.

Ad Text:
Job Description

Our Finance Transformation team are trusted advisors to CFOs and their Finance teams supporting them to meet the challenges of a complex and rapidly evolving business environment. We help them navigate change to deliver efficiency, insight and value to their businesses. Our diverse and multidisciplinary team brings together skill sets across Finance.

The role we specifically require is within the Finance Transformation service offering. Finance Transformation is a strategic assessment of an organisation’s finance operating model including systems, processes, people and operations, aimed at increasing efficiency and effectiveness, enhancing decision-making, and aligning financial functions with broader business objectives using digital technologies and other improvements.

Your Opportunity:

With continued growth and strong pipeline, we are now seeking a Director to join our team, with a focus to managing Finance Transformation engagements across ERP and EPM solutions covering planning, budgeting and forecasting, reporting (Performance and Financial), data analytics and insights, and integration of AI in Finance. Alongside delivering exceptional client outcomes, you will drive business development activities by building strong relationships and identifying new opportunities.

You will work with some of the country’s leading clients as well as the wider national team, in a positive, collaborative and team focused environment. This role is ideally suited to candidates who have prior finance transformation experience as well as experience leading cross-functional teams ideally in a Consulting environment or in a transformation capacity, and who are seeking an opportunity to broaden their experience working with different clients, as well as undertaking challenging and rewarding work harnessing their leadership, analytical and problem-solving skills.

Your Experience

Recent experience managing in areas of finance operations, shared services, financial planning & analysis, and accounting ideally in a consulting environment or in a transformation program.

Understanding of leading practice across the finance operating model (e.g. in relation to processes and controls, systems, service delivery model) and deep understanding of process dependencies across other functional areas (for example sourcing, human resources etc)

Ability to provide strategic insights and support decision making across core finance operating mode

Financial and management reporting experience to support reporting strategy

Deep understanding of how a system implementation project is delivered (e.g. phases, core teams, standard deliverables)

Advanced ERP / EPM / Cloud technology experience through previous engagements or industry experience (e.g. Oracle. Microsoft, SAP)

Ability to articulate functional business requirements to technical requirements and facilitate solution design and development

Experience delivering end to end EPM engagements including technical build and deployment

Additional Information

Ability to Travel as required

Applicants must be currently authorised to work in Australia without the need for visa sponsorship now or in the future

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Senior Business Systems Analyst – Exchange Migration
Ad Text:
PM-Partners group is a specialist Project Management Consultancy. We have a unique way of running projects and providing training and advice, so our clients get the best results with less cost and risk. Each year we deliver over $3B of projects, train over 10,000 people, and help some of Australia’s leading brands improve their PMOs.




A Senior Business Analyst is required to support a large-scale Exchange migration within a Cyber Security team. This role will lead business and functional analysis across email security, archiving, retention and compliance, ensuring a smooth transition with minimal disruption to the business. 

 

The Business Analyst will own requirements definition, application and process mapping, business acceptance criteria, and delivery of the Requirements Traceability Matrix and Business Case. The role will work closely with architects, vendors and stakeholders, contributing to change and risk impact assessments and supporting high-level solution design. 




Key Requirements 

7+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst, with exposure to cyber or security initiatives 
Strong experience in business and functional requirements, process modelling and application mapping 
Understanding of mail flow, system connectors and email archiving/retention 
Experience working across Microsoft 365 security platforms (EOP, Defender for O365, Purview, Entra ID) 
Proven delivery in complex, regulated environments with distributed teams 
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement and documentation skills 

What we can offer you! 

Culture: A fun, fast paced, collaborative delivery environment 
People: A group of talented, experienced, and dedicated Consultants to work by your side with a dedicated Relationship Manager 
Passion: Ability to band together when under pressure to deliver first class results to clients 
Transparency: Open door policy 
Professional Development: On the job development and access to certifications in our Training practice 
Care and Support: On-going support and advice from experienced PM-Partners Consultants

If you feel you meet our selection criteria, please submit your resume to Paul Woodhead at PM-Partners via LinkedIn or SEEK application or email –  paulw@pm-partners.com.au

Job Title: Senior or Associate Geospatial Analyst - Perth
Ad Text:
Shape the Future with CDM Smith Australia – Senior or Associate Geospatial Analyst

Are you ready to leave your mark on the world and build a legacy for generations to come?

At CDM Smith Australia, we believe meaningful careers start with connection. We aren’t simply hiring, we’re partnering with passionate professionals who want to make a real difference. Your expertise, vision and values are what matter most to us. If you’re looking for more than just a job, join us to shape the future of environmental services across Western Australia and beyond.

About You

Between 7 and 10 years of GIS experience, preferably in a consulting environment (Senior Level).

10+ years of GIS experience, preferably in a consulting environment (Associate Level). 

Tertiary qualifications in GIS, Environmental Science, or equivalent.

Extensive knowledge of and experience with Esri GIS software (e.g. ArcGIS Pro, Enterprise, AGOL etc).

Proven ability to undertake business development in a consulting environment from opportunity identification to bid delivery.

Python experience (desirable) and FME experience (desirable).

A passion for process automation and solution development. 

Creative problem-solving skills to work autonomously, and as part of a team, and a genuine interest in innovation, continual learning and improvement.

Experience, or the ability, to take ownership of a work front and proactively collaborate with stakeholders to deliver outcomes and improve processes in a dynamic environment. 

Have robust analytical skills, with experience in the management, manipulation, analysis and presentation of spatial data.

Solid organisational and time management skills.

Outstanding communication skills, and confidence in building positive relationships.

Ability to grasp new concepts quickly, be adaptable and flexible, and contribute individually and within a team environment to the success of a project.

Full legal working rights within Australia.

Why CDM Smith Australia?

Shape the Future with Us in Western Australia
We’re tackling Australia’s most pressing environmental, water, and digital challenges head-on. Here, your work will have genuine impact—not only for our clients, but for communities and the planet itself. You’ll be empowered to develop innovative solutions, drive technical excellence, and build a sustainable future for Western Australia. We are seeking talented Senior or Associate GIS Analyst to coordinate and deliver GIS analysis and spatial solutions across diverse environmental and engineering projects. Based in our Perth office or client sites, you’ll work closely with project teams to scope and implement integrated spatial solutions that enhance project outcomes.

In this role, you’ll also play a key part in driving innovation and improving spatial services, collaborating with our Technical Practice Leader – Digital to identify opportunities for smarter delivery. This is your chance to combine technical expertise with creativity, shaping solutions that make a real difference.

Rewards: Referral bonuses, employee discounts, and benefits programs.

Belonging: Be part of a global, employee-owned consulting firm committed to diversity, inclusion and a positive workplace culture.

 

Join Us – Make Your Mark

Ready to be part of a team where your insight, expertise and ideas truly matter? Where client relationships are built on trust, and solutions are shaped by passion and knowledge? At CDM Smith Australia, we’re growing because we invest in our people and our clients by delivering fit-for-purpose, sustainable answers for industry’s toughest problems.

We welcome applicants from all backgrounds. Diversity, technical ability, integrity and innovation are the hallmarks of our team. If you want to be heard, valued and inspired, let's shape your NOW and your NEXT, together.

Let’s get started: For more information or a confidential chat, reach out to Senior Human Resources Business Partner – Sharra Holborow at 0467 034 631 or holborowsj@cdmsmith.com.

At CDM Smith, we Listen, Think, Deliver.

We can't wait to hear your story.

Solution Designer – Credit Risk & Data Platforms

Location: Sydney
Start Date: January 2025
Employment Type: Contract
Priority: Active Hiring

We are seeking an experienced Solution Designer to play a critical role in designing and delivering enterprise-scale data and analytics solutions within a complex Credit Risk and Banking environment. This position will work across business and technology domains to engineer robust, reusable, and high-value data products that support risk models, analytics, and regulatory outcomes.

About the Role

As a Solution Designer, you will be responsible for defining end-to-end solution architectures across multiple platforms and technologies. You will collaborate closely with Credit Risk stakeholders, service owners, and engineering teams to ensure solutions align with enterprise standards, design principles, and strategic objectives.

This role requires deep experience in data engineering, risk analytics platforms, cloud technologies, and large-scale delivery within regulated environments.

Key Responsibilities

Design and implement cross-functional, enterprise-grade data solutions across multiple technologies and platforms.

Engineer reusable enterprise data products across sourcing, data quality, modelling, integration, and consumption layers.

Identify, define, and oversee delivery of common enterprise components to improve solution consistency, maintainability, and delivery efficiency.

Define solution architectures spanning:

SAS platforms and modelling tools

Hadoop and Big Data ecosystems

Azure and Azure Machine Learning

Teradata Data Warehouse

ETL and integration tools (e.g. Informatica)

Business Intelligence tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau)

Partner with Credit Risk business stakeholders, service owners, technology leads, and Line of Business leaders to prioritise and refine requirements and backlogs.

Ensure solution designs comply with enterprise architecture standards, data governance, and risk controls.

Work with business teams to understand credit risk data elements, including reference data, metadata, and data lineage.

Guide Agile delivery teams through design, development, testing, deployment, and support using modern DevOps practices.

Skills and Experience

To be successful in this role, you will demonstrate:

3+ years’ experience working in large and complex Credit Risk and/or Banking environments.

10+ years’ experience delivering business and technology solutions involving complex data engineering and processing.

5+ years’ advanced experience with SQL and SAS, including:

Base SAS, SAS Macro

SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide

SAS Management Console and SAS Platform administration

5+ years’ experience with modern data and engineering technologies, including:

Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase

Python, Java, Spring Boot

Git, Flink, Cosmos DB, Akka, Scala, SQL, Synapse

Strong experience in data warehousing, modelling, and integration tools such as Informatica and Sterling.

Familiarity with business intelligence platforms including IBM Cognos/TM1, Power BI, and Tableau.

Proven experience designing solutions for cloud platforms, preferably Microsoft Azure, including serverless architectures.

Experience designing and supporting Risk Models and Analytics using:

SAS RFW, SAS Risk Stratum, SAS Viya

Azure Machine Learning

Hands-on experience with DevOps pipelines, particularly Azure DevOps and Jenkins.

Ad Text:
Shape whole-of-government agricultural policy with data-driven insights that elevate priorities, sharpen strategy and strengthen outcomes across the sector.

About the role

The Director, Straegic Policy and Insights is responsible for leading a key policy team to provide strategic policy, insights and advice across the agriculture portfolio and Cabinet and intergovernmental matters, alongside planning, risk management and reporting. It will work to provide policy with an ‘agriculture first' lens but that take a whole of department, and whole of government view to ensure government and sectoral priorities progress.

This suite of business functions will work to streamline group coordination while enhancing policy, planning and reporting outcomes.

The branch is responsible for and has capacity to to achieve program outcomes with a dedicated focus on providing data and insights at a branch, division and Agriculture Victoria-wide that drives the development of evidence-based policy.

About you:

To be successful in the role, you will have:

An appropriate tertiary qualification in a subject-related discipline and relevant post graduate qualifications would be well regarded.

About the Group

Agriculture Victoria partners with farmers, industries, communities, government and research organisations to grow, modernise, protect and promote Victoria's agriculture. Agriculture Victoria forms part of an extensive local, national and international system to protect animal welfare and biosecurity, deliver policy, programs and research to understand emerging agricultural challenges like climate change, manage critical transitions such as forestry industry and food safety reform, promote domestic animal management, and enable economic productivity through innovative farming systems, skills and technologies.

This is a fixed term position available for a period of up to years. The work location for this position is flexible within Victoria with hybrid work arrangements available.

To be considered for this position, applicants are encouraged to submit a resume and cover letter (no longer than 2 pages) summarising their skills and relevant experience.

For further information, please refer to the attached position description or call David Burns, Executive Director, Agriculture Policy and Programs on 0429 263 234 or email david.g.burns@agriculture.vic.gov.au.

Applications close at midnight on Sunday, 11 January 2026.

Other relevant information:

Preferred candidates will be required to:

undertake pre-employment screening, including completion of a Declaration and Consent form and a National Police Check
have their misconduct declarations validated, irrespective of whether misconduct has been declared or not
provide at least two appropriate referees, including their current direct line manager or where relevant (i.e. because they are not employed) most recent direct line manager in accordance with the requirements set out in executive reference checks.
provide evidence of their right to work in Australia

For more information about the pre-screening requirements for this position, please refer to the position description.

To be eligible for appointment to this role, applicants will possess corresponding work rights for the advertised employment period. Appointment to an ongoing position is only available to an Australian/New Zealand citizen or an Australian Permanent Resident.

Ad Text:
ASIS is Australia’s overseas secret intelligence collection agency. Its mission is to protect and promote Australia’s vital interests through the provision of intelligence services as directed by the Australian Government.

ASIS employs people in a wide range of roles, including technologists. These roles require dynamic team players who enjoy working with stakeholders, team members and individually on projects. ASIS is looking for people who will be able to meet tight deadlines and work to support ASIS priorities. Successful candidates will have excellent coordination and administration skills, excellent verbal and written communication skills; and, strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills. Relevant tertiary qualifications and demonstrable experience will be highly regarded.

ASIS values workplace diversity and is committed to providing a supportive, inclusive and respectful work environment. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People, women, people with disabilities, people that identify as LGBTIQ+ and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds. We offer a competitive salary packing, including 22 days annual leave, shutdown between Christmas and New Year’s Day, 15.4% employer superannuation contribution, access to flex time (up to Level 6 only) and generous paid maternity/paternity leave.

Positions for these roles are based in Canberra and/or Adelaide CBD. These roles require the successful applicants to obtain and maintain a security clearance.  

AI, Machine Learning, Data Science & Analytics (Level 4—EL1)

Are you keen to design and develop world-class capabilities, turning data into knowledge and operational outcomes? Are you passionate about building solutions to allow data to tell its story? ASIS offers an opportunity to achieve these goals in an uncompromisingly unique environment. As a Data Professional in ASIS, you will have the chance to actively enable our operational teams to make the best use of ASIS’s unique data assets. ASIS leverages the wide world of open-source software and supplements it with our own development to deliver the bespoke tools required for the ASIS mission. Among our core languages are Python, Scala, Java, C++, Rust and JavaScript. Our toolset includes Spring, PyTorch, Tensorflow, Apache Spark, Apache Accumulo, Apache Hadoop, Apache NiFi, Apache Solr, Ansible and Git. We leverage structured and unstructured data, including geospatial and multilingual data sets of varying quality. Ideal candidates will be extraordinarily innovative, self-motivated and keen to use these toolsets to craft new systems that are simply not found in any other organisation. If this sounds like an environment you could thrive in, then apply for one of these unique positions.

Application Levels

A Level 4 candidate would be expected to be new to the area and work under the guidance and supervision of a more senior officer.

A candidate at the Level 5 level would be expected to have one to two years real-world experience and will be working under some supervision.

A Level 6 level candidate would be expected to have more experience and operate with limited supervision within a core group of developers.

A candidate at the EL1 level is expected to have substantial experience, and some deep technical expertise. They operate entirely independently and have the capacity to fulfil leadership roles as required.

Specialisations

We have a number of positions available including:

· Data Scientists at Level 4 to EL1; and

· MLOps Engineers at Level 5 to EL1

· Machine Learning Scientists at Level 4 to EL1; and

· Applied Mathematicians at Level 5 to EL1

Employment Type: Full time


#LI-RM1

Lead Data Engineer
(Initial 12 month FTC - With a view to turn perm)
Greenfield Microsoft Fabric Build. Reporting to CIO

A leading organisation is standing up a brand new Data and Analytics function. This is a rare greenfield opportunity for a Data Engineer who wants to shape an entire ecosystem from day one.

You will work directly with the CIO. You will own the design, build, and evolution of a modern Azure and Microsoft Fabric environment. The strategy is already mapped. Now they need someone with the technical strength and business mindset to bring it to life.

This role suits someone who thrives in autonomy, sees the commercial value of data, and enjoys being the expert in the room.


What you will be doing
Build scalable data pipelines and models across Azure, Fabric and enterprise systems.
Integrate core operational platforms. Salesforce, JD Edwards, SiteTracker and others.
Shape the data architecture. Create models that support high-quality reporting and analytics.
Automate workflows using Python, SQL and REST APIs.
Lift data governance, quality and documentation as foundational pillars of the function.
Partner with senior stakeholders and translate business needs into practical technical outcomes.
Evaluate and introduce modern tooling to accelerate analytics maturity.
Support early Power BI development.
AI-Ready by Design

The foundations you build must be future-proof. The business is already experimenting with Microsoft Copilot and has an AI specialist in-house. The long-term vision is for data engineering and applied AI to merge. Your architecture choices today will enable automation, decision-intelligence and ML-driven workflows tomorrow.


What makes this role exciting
Greenfield environment. You build the blueprint.
Direct line to the CIO.
First hire into a brand new Data and Analytics function.
High likelihood of converting to permanent.
Strong, people-first culture.
Clear path toward an AI-enabled operating model.
What you bring
Experience across Azure, Fabric and modern cloud architectures.
At least six months in a live Microsoft Fabric environment.
Expertise across data modelling, dimensional modelling and scalable architecture.
Python, SQL and REST API capability.
Commercial thinking. Ability to engage senior stakeholders cleanly.
Curiosity around AI and how strong data foundations enable intelligent automation.
Ideally coming from a digital infrastructure or telecommunications infrastructure background
Why this role matters

This hire will determine how the organisation uses data for years to come. You will shape everything. Pipelines. Models. Governance. Architecture. AI-readiness.

If you want to step into a role where you influence, build and own a modern, AI-ready data environment from scratch. This is it.

Role description

Dhelkaya Health is seeking a skilled Business Analyst to join our Finance Directorate and play a critical role in driving informed decision-making across the organisation.

In this pivotal position, you will:

Deliver high-quality financial analysis and activity insights
Develop business cases and financial models to support sustainability and performance

About you

Tertiary qualifications in Accounting, Finance, Commerce, Data Analytics or related field.

Previous experience in a similar role

 

Culture and Benefits

Dhelkaya Health is located on Dja Dja Wurrung country in regional Victoria. Just a short drive from Bendigo and easily accessed via public transport, the area is brimming with culture that blends the old with the new. Steeped in rich history, the town boasts a vibrant arts scene, historic architecture and is part of the Bendigo Region UNESCO City of Gastronomy. 

Surrounded by scenic trails and a unique natural environment that includes historic goldfields, outdoor enthusiasts can immerse themselves in the beauty of the natural world. Combined with a wide range of sporting clubs and outdoor recreation opportunities, the community offers a rich, diverse culture to enjoy.

From community events celebrating local festivals to grassroots initiatives fostering inclusivity and diversity, this is a place where people come together. At Dhelkaya Health, you'll enjoy all this and a flexible work environment with access to career development pathways that suit your life goals. Stress-free parking: at no-cost close to your place of work. 
Salary packaging: to maximise your earnings with options to package meals, entertainment, rent/mortgage repayments, and more.

Health and wellbeing: through a supported work environment that prioritises work-life balance and a health and well-being program that includes an Employee Assistance Program.
Building meaningful connections: through the Dhelkaya Health Social Club and a variety of staff events and activities throughout the year held in a friendly, inclusive environment where everyone feels welcome.

Job Title: Business Analyst - HCM, 12 Month fixed term engagement
Ad Text:
Leading ASX-listed Services company requires an experienced Business Analyst to join their team and play a key role in the implementation and ongoing optimisation of their Human Capital Management (HCM) system and processes on a 12 month fixed term engagement.

In this role, you will work closely with a broad range of stakeholders to understand business needs, translate requirements into clear solutions, and ensure the successful delivery of HCM initiatives that support our people and business objectives.

On a day-to-day basis, you will:

Collaborate with business stakeholders to gather, document and analyse requirements related to the HCM system.
Act as a trusted bridge between technical teams and business units, ensuring solutions align with strategic goals.
Facilitate workshops and stakeholder meetings to elicit, validate and prioritise requirements.
Produce high-quality documentation, including business process models, functional specifications and use cases.
Support the implementation, testing and deployment of HCM solutions, ensuring a smooth and effective transition.
Identify opportunities for process improvement and provide practical, value-driven recommendations.
Stay current with industry trends and emerging HCM technologies.
To be successful in this role, you will bring:

Proven experience working as a Business Analyst, ideally within an HCM or HR systems environment.
Strong knowledge of leading HCM platforms such as Workday, SAP SuccessFactors, Oracle HCM Cloud, or similar.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with strong attention to detail.
Outstanding communication and stakeholder management capabilities.
Experience using business process modelling tools and methodologies.
A solid understanding of HR processes, including payroll, recruitment, talent management and the employee lifecycle.
Desirable

Relevant certifications such as CBAP or HCM product-specific certifications.
A hybrid work environment consisting of 3 days in the office, 2 days from home, is on offer.

Public transport, consisting of buses and metro is only a 5 mins walk away.

Camden Council is one of Australia’s fastest-growing local government areas, delivering major digital and data modernisation initiatives to support a thriving and connected community.

With significant investment in Azure cloud capabilities, the Council is building a scalable, modern data platform to enable high-quality analytics and evidence-based decision making.

We are excited to partner with Camden Council to recruit an experienced Senior Data Engineer who will play a pivotal role in driving this transformation.

The Opportunity

As the Senior Data Engineer, you will be a key technical lead within the Digital Technology & Innovation Branch, responsible for architecting and delivering end-to-end data solutions across Camden Council’s Azure environment.

This is a hands-on role where you will design, develop, and optimise data pipelines, establish best-practice data engineering standards, and enable advanced analytics across the organisation.  You will work closely with the Team Leader – Data & Insights, the CIO, and cross-functional stakeholders to build a sustainable and scalable data ecosystem.

Key Responsibilities
Design, build, and maintain end-to-end data pipelines using Azure Data Factory.
Transform raw data into high-quality, structured assets using Azure Databricks, PySpark, Delta Lake, and Spark SQL.
Manage data across Bronze, Silver, Gold layers in Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2.
Develop and optimise data models to support analytics and Power BI reporting.
Enable advanced analytics by delivering clean, reliable, production-ready datasets.
Implement CI/CD pipelines and Git-based development practices.
Uphold data governance, including cataloging and lineage through Azure Purview/Unity Catalog.
Partner closely with business units to translate requirements into scalable data solutions.
Support platform optimisation, performance tuning, and cost management.
About You

You’re an experienced Senior Data Engineer who thrives in cloud-native environments and enjoys building enterprise-scale data solutions from the ground up.  You will bring:

5+ years’ experience in data engineering, including ETL/ELT, data modelling, and Azure data architecture.
Hands-on experience with Azure Databricks (PySpark, Spark SQL, Delta Lake).
Strong expertise in Azure Data Factory and orchestrating end-to-end pipelines.
Proficiency in Python and SQL.
Experience integrating data from APIs, on-prem databases, and CSV/JSON files.
Familiarity with Azure Purview/Unity Catalog and data governance frameworks.
Experience with CI/CD pipelines and Git-based workflows.
Excellent communication and problem-solving skills.
Desirable:

Experience with Power BI, Jira, Confluence, or local government systems (Authority, CAMMS).
Why Join Camden Council?
Be at the forefront of Camden’s enterprise data transformation.
Work with modern Azure technologies in a forward-thinking organisation.
Hybrid work model – 3 days onsite in Oran Park.
Supportive leadership, strong team culture, and impactful community-focused work.
Competitive salary and 2-year fixed term security.
Click 'Apply Now' for immediate consideration.
